      <item>
        <title>Personal blog</title>
        <dc:creator><![CDATA[luisherranz]]></dc:creator>
        <description><![CDATA[
            <p>Hey <a class="mention" href="https://community.frontity.org/u/jesus.designer">@jesus.designer</a>, I’ve been taking a look at your site again. I think you can improve the LightHouse score if:</p>
<ol>
<li>You can update to the latest version of Frontity (which fixes a problem with the lazy loading of images).</li>
<li>Disqus is loading a lot of JS/CSS files, so you could use our <code>useInView</code> hook to lazy load the it when the user scrolls down. Something like this (I’m doing this from memory, I haven’t tested it):</li>
</ol>
<pre><code>const Comments = () =&gt; {
  // It appears 600px before this div enters the viewport.
  const [isVisible, ref] = useInView({ rootMargin: "-600px" });
  return (
    &lt;div ref={ref}&gt;
      {isVisible &amp;&amp; &lt;Disqus /&gt;}
    &lt;/div&gt;
}
</code></pre>
<ol start="3">
<li>Instead of using a CSS request to load the fonts, you can include them in your Frontity project and embed them in the HTML. That way you save a blocking CSS request and several Font requests.</li>
</ol>
<p>What do you think? Do you want to try? <img src="https://community.frontity.org/images/emoji/apple/slight_smile.png?v=9" title=":slight_smile:" class="emoji" alt=":slight_smile:"></p>
          <p><a href="https://community.frontity.org/t/personal-blog/360/24">Read full topic</a></p>
        ]]></description>
        <link>https://community.frontity.org/t/personal-blog/360/24</link>
        <pubDate>Thu, 19 Dec 2019 10:15:17 +0000</pubDate>
        <guid isPermaLink="false">community.frontity.org-post-360-24</guid>
        <source url="https://community.frontity.org/t/personal-blog/360.rss">Personal blog</source>
